ermedial transpositions, the writings of Sherman Alexie, Chang-rae Lee, and Jamaica Kincaid insist upon a differentiation between the representation of cultural sign systems or subject positions and the dramatization of individual gestures of authorship. As such, they form a postethnic literary constellation, further probed in the epilogue of the study focused on Dave Eggers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAutorschaft. 4aGegenwartsliteratur. 4aPostkolonialismus. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aAuthorship.  aContemporary Literature.  aPostcolonialism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023846408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW0 cEPUBz97831104091160 cprintz978311037370740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036848240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110368482423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110368482/original  a978-3-11-023846-4  DGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBAC